  "details": "[WHY]\nExplore new use case for Gemini Enterprise adoption\nTo enable Australia Post to onboard new team members using a conversational interface for service requests.\nTo replace traditional form-filling in ServiceNow with a more intuitive, \"agentic\" experience.\nTo validate that an AI agent can manage state, reason through complex policies, and handle real-time user corrections before executing actions\n\n[WHAT]\nBuilding Pass Request Agent\nIntent Recognition: Identifies when a hiring manager needs to order a security badge for a new hire.\nPolicy Lookup: Dynamically checks ServiceNow tables for specific requirements (e.g., office location, access level, and photo).\nState Management: Allows the user to update variables mid-conversation (e.g., changing contact hours from \"9-10\" to \"3-4\") without restarting the entire flow.\nExecution: Submits the final payload to ServiceNow and returns a Service Request ID to the user.\nLaptop Request Agent\nContextual Procurement: Identifies the need for hardware based on the employee's location (e.g., AusPost Head Office).\nDynamic Validation: Queries the SNOW API to present only valid, currently available laptop models to the user.\nSeamless Integration: Automates the submission of the Service Request once a model is selected and provides the tracking ID.\n\n[HOW]\nThe solution utilizes the ADK (Agent Development Kit) Orchestrator to manage the conversation flow.\nAuthentication: Users authenticate via ServiceNow OAuth2 through the Gemini Enterprise UI, with direct integration with customer ServiceNow sandbox API.\nData Retrieval: The agent fetches user details (like sys_id) from the sys_user table and policy requirements from the variables table.\nIntegration Stack: The workflow integrates Gemini Enterprise, Agent Engine, and Application Integration/Connectors to bridge the gap between the LLM and the ServiceNow non-prod instance.\nTooling: Employs Function Tooling to handle specific tasks like file uploads (for ID photos) and record insertion into the sc_request table.",
